@NODE "Revision history"

@{B}Revision history@{UB}

Version 1.0 released 25-Dec-1995

 - First public release.

Version 1.1 released 11-Mar-1996

 - Base64Decode is now about 10% faster. This means that it is now just as
   fast as uuOut (by Nicolas Dade) is with decoding uuencoded files. This
   was a goal of mine. :-)

 - Fixed bug in non-base64 code skipping routine in Base64Decode.

 - Changed MIME header generated by Base64Encode. The name of the encoded
   file is now put on the Content-Type line.

 - Base64Decode wil now try to extract the TO filename from the MIME header
   in the message body if you only specify a directory path for the TO
   argument.

 - Included Base64Decode.spot. An ARexx script for Spot to decode a base64
   encoded binary from the current message.

@ENDNODE
